<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-465-678  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 465 678.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>DEC User  April 1990 p53(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The software tools' software tool. (Software Review) (VirtualSoftware Factory from Systematica) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bloor, Robin.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Virtual Software Factory (VSF), from Systematica, is arevolutionary product in the computer aided software engineering(Case) market and for software development in general.andP;  VSFimplements analysis and design methodology in a language calledCantor.andP;  Cantor is a language-description language that allows thedeveloper to define a methodology.andP;  Case tools develop fromdefinition of the elements of a method, the associated rules forcombining them, and the notation that is to be used for eachelement of the method.andP;  VSF gives developers the functionality tomove objects, enter data, generate reports, and move from onerepresentation to another.andP;  VSF uses what is called a fullyconnected, fully inverted, semantic net, rather than aconventional relational data base.andP;  This feature provides anapproximately linear performance curve as the number of crossreferences increases.andP;  The biggest problem with VSF is thesix-figure price.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Systematica (products).andO;Product:   Virtual Software Factory (Program development software).andO;Topic:     EvaluationComputer-Aided Software EngineeringProgram Development ToolsData Base Management Systems.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Virtual Software Factory's Methods Workbench embodies VSF. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>